d successful prevention of criminality, ghettoisation, extremism and even radicalisation through reasonable immigrant integration.Key FeaturesIntroduces the schools, tools and concepts needed to understand nationalismCovers both classic foundational theories and more recent theories of nationalism and national identityIncludes chapter-length case studies of 6 countries: America, Russia, India, Britain, South Africa and PeruEngages both theoretically and empirically with the study of nationalism todayShows the impact of immigration and globalisation on nationalism and national identity  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aPolitics. 70(DE-588)4013960-80(DE-627)1063415020(DE-576)20890610XaEinwanderung2gnd 70(DE-588)4041282-90(DE-627)1041624300(DE-576)209044284aNationalbewusstsein2gnd 70(DE-588)4041331-70(DE-627)1062196420(DE-576)209044500aNationalstaat2gnd 70(DE-588)4129681-30(DE-627)1057081350(DE-576)209612525aKulturnation2gnd 70(DE-588)4151434-80(DE-627)1042621840(DE-576)20978816XaEinwanderer2gnd 70(DE-588)4162051-30(DE-627)1048191540(DE-576)209870583aInternationale Migration2gnd 70(DE-588)4171218-30(DE-627)1043211990(DE-576)209935588aNationalitätenstaat2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Nationalism & Patriotism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107804200 cprintz978147441340440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147441342840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474413428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474413428/original  a978-3-11-078042-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-a